The paper discusses natural language generation, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of Integer Linear Programming (ILP) is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) for optimization problems. The paper also discusses the generation of compact texts, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and summarization (cs.SI).
